# Testing a cheap mobile antenna

It took a while, but I finally got a [Bingfu dual-band mobile antenna](https://a.co/d/0gd4XHSu) from Amazon. Its a cheap product but had good reviews. Since I've been struggling to get good reception with my rubber duck, I thought it would be good to check this out.

Came with 2 sets of radials, 3 short, 3 long, and zero instructions. So I assumed (and checked with ChatGPT) that the longer ones were dor the 2m config, so those are the ones I installed.

The antenna comes with a huge coax, like 10-12 feet, so its gonna be weird to run it into the car, but it allows me to have the antenna outside while I comfortably sit indoors.

So far im getting good reception from W1BOS and K1BOS, which sould work, but now im getting a nice clean signal from KC1US which is near Reading! I never heard this repeater with the rubber ducky.

![Antenna](../assets/pics/Bingfu_antenna_test.jpg)

I'll figure out how yo mount it in the car next time I go out for a wardrive. But so far so good!

73, KC1ZTY out.
